The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gill invites Real 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Gill invites Real 
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: After Bayern Munich, it could be the turn of Real Madrid to play an exhibition match in Calcutta on the invitation of the Union sports minister MS Gill.         
	Talking to the reporters on the sidelines of the state sports ministers conference, Gill said he has requested Real Madrid president Ramon Calderon to play a match in Calcutta.         
	I met him during the Wimbledon final and asked him whether he was ready to play in India. He said he was keen, Gill said.                                                                                                                          
